text: Fountainbleau is an unincorporated community in Andrew County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Fountainbleau was established in 1875, and remained in operation until 1905. The community was named after the Palace of Fontainebleau, in France. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Andrew County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Fountainbleau, Missouri
